WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:55.312 --> 00:00:59.073
<i>My planet Arrakis is so beautiful
when the sun is low.</i>

3
00:01:02.312 --> 00:01:07.632
<i>Rolling over the sands… you
can see spice in the air.</i>

4
00:01:20.892 --> 00:01:24.772
<i>At nightfall. the spice harvesters land.</i>

5
00:01:26.052 --> 00:01:30.572
<i>The outsiders race against time
to avoid the heat of the day.</i>

6
00:01:39.592 --> 00:01:43.312
<i>They ravage our lands in front of our eyes.</i>

7
00:01:43.392 --> 00:01:47.152
<i>Their cruelty to my people is all I've known.</i>

8
00:01:52.132 --> 00:01:54.492
<i>These outsiders. the Harkonnens.</i>

9
00:01:54.572 --> 00:01:56.492
<i>came long before I was born.</i>

10
00:01:56.573 --> 00:01:58.412
<i>By controlling spice production.</i>

11
00:01:58.493 --> 00:02:00.252
<i>they became obscenely rich.</i>

12
00:02:00.332 --> 00:02:02.932
<i>Richer than the Emperor himself.</i>

13
00:02:45.392 --> 00:02:48.752
<i>Our warriors couldn't free Arrakis
from the Harkonnens.</i>

14
00:02:48.832 --> 00:02:50.072
<i>but one day.</i>

15
00:02:50.072 --> 00:02:53.272
<i>by Imperial decree. they were gone.</i>

16
00:03:00.132 --> 00:03:02.652
<i>Why did the Emperor choose this path?</i>

17
00:03:03.892 --> 00:03:06.292
<i>And who will our next oppressors be?</i>

18
00:03:57.952 --> 00:03:59.632
It's good you're up early.

19
00:04:00.952 --> 00:04:03.952
Your father wants you in full dress
before the Emperor's Herald arrives.

20
00:04:04.592 --> 00:04:06.032
Full dress?

21
00:04:06.912 --> 00:04:08.512
Military?

22
00:04:08.592 --> 00:04:11.032
Ceremonial.

23
00:04:11.612 --> 00:04:14.332
Why do we have to go through all this
when it's already been decided?

24
00:04:15.372 --> 00:04:16.772
Ceremony.

25
00:04:17.372 --> 00:04:18.772
Mm.

26
00:04:19.672 --> 00:04:21.072
Thank you.

27
00:04:22.072 --> 00:04:24.352
If you want it. make me give it to you.

28
00:04:25.672 --> 00:04:26.632
Use The Voice.

29
00:04:26.632 --> 00:04:28.392
Mom. I just woke up.

30
00:04:36.271 --> 00:04:38.232
Give me the water.

31
00:04:38.312 --> 00:04:40.512
The glass can't hear you. Command me.

32
00:05:08.092 --> 00:05:10.252
[Weird Sounding Voice]
Give me the water.

33
00:05:22.711 --> 00:05:24.111
Almost.

34
00:05:24.252 --> 00:05:25.652
Almost?

35
00:05:25.652 --> 00:05:27.972
Bene Gesserit skills take years to learn. Paul.

36
00:05:28.052 --> 00:05:30.812
- Mm-hmm.
- You look tired.

37
00:05:31.732 --> 00:05:33.132
More dreams?

38
00:05:38.291 --> 00:05:39.691
No.

39
00:05:42.972 --> 00:05:46.412
<i>Extreme temperatures and treacherous
weather events</i>

40
00:05:46.492 --> 00:05:50.092
<i>make life outside the cities
of Arrakis truly hostile.</i>

41
00:05:50.172 --> 00:05:53.612
<i>with sandstorms powerful enough
to cut through metal.</i>

42
00:05:53.691 --> 00:05:59.812
<i>Only the native tribes known as the Fremen
have adapted well enough to survive.</i>

43
00:05:59.892 --> 00:06:04.172
<i>Preferring to inhabit the remotest
regions of Arrakis.</i>

44
00:06:04.251 --> 00:06:11.052
<i>the Fremen share the deep desert with the giant sandworms known to the Fremen as</i> Shai-Hulud.

45
00:06:11.632 --> 00:06:18.712
<i>Long exposure to spice has given the tribe their
characteristic blue eyes. the Eyes of Ibad.</i>

46
00:06:19.792 --> 00:06:26.632
<i>Little else is known of the Fremen. except
that they are dangerous and unreliable.</i>

47
00:06:26.712 --> 00:06:31.192
<i>Fremen attacks make spice harvesting
extremely hazardous.</i>

48
00:06:31.771 --> 00:06:36.732
<i>For the Fremen. spice is the sacred
hallucinogen which preserves life</i>

49
00:06:36.732 --> 00:06:39.412
<i>and brings enormous health benefits.</i>

50
00:06:39.992 --> 00:06:43.672
<i>For the Imperium. spice is used by the navigators</i>

51
00:06:43.752 --> 00:06:48.232
<i>of the Spacing Guild to find safe
paths between the stars.</i>

52
00:06:48.311 --> 00:06:52.431
<i>Without spice. interstellar travel is impossible.</i>

53
00:06:52.512 --> 00:06:57.072
<i>making it by far the most valuable
substance in the universe.</i>

54
00:07:46.472 --> 00:07:47.871
Smile. Gurney.

55
00:07:48.552 --> 00:07:50.511
I am smiling.

56
00:07:51.432 --> 00:07:55.471
How much will it cost them. traveling
all this way for this formality?

57
00:07:55.552 --> 00:07:56.912
Three Guild Navigators.

58
00:07:56.912 --> 00:08:00.432
A total of one point forty-six million.
sixty-two solaris. round trip.

59
00:08:17.012 --> 00:08:22.092
By the grace of Shaddam IV of House Corrino.
ascendant to the Golden Lion Throne

60
00:08:22.172 --> 00:08:29.051
of Padishah Emperor of the Known Universe. I
stand before you as Herald of the change.

61
00:08:29.132 --> 00:08:31.931
We are witnessed by members of the Imperial court.

62
00:08:32.012 --> 00:08:37.652
representatives of the Spacing Guild
and a sister of the Bene Gesserit.

63
00:08:39.552 --> 00:08:41.751
The Emperor has spoken.

64
00:08:43.151 --> 00:08:50.712
“House Atreides shall immediately take control
of Arrakis and serve as its steward.”

65
00:08:52.352 --> 00:08:54.192
Do you accept?

66
00:09:03.992 --> 00:09:06.751
We are house Atreides.

67
00:09:06.832 --> 00:09:10.992
There is no call we do not answer.
there is no faith that we betray.

68
00:09:11.072 --> 00:09:15.872
The Emperor asks us to bring peace to Arrakis.

69
00:09:16.451 --> 00:09:18.771
House Atreides accepts.

70
00:09:18.852 --> 00:09:23.051
Atreides! Atreides! Atreides!

71
00:09:23.132 --> 00:09:27.411
Atreides! Atreides! Atreides!

72
00:09:35.172 --> 00:09:36.692
Your seal.

73
00:10:12.472 --> 00:10:13.872
So. it's done?

74
00:10:15.272 --> 00:10:16.672
It's done.

75
00:10:43.731 --> 00:10:45.131
How was it?

76
00:10:45.172 --> 00:10:46.572
<i>Stabilizers are too loose.</i>

77
00:10:46.611 --> 00:10:48.612
- We'll dial it in.
- <i>Thank you. my friend.</i>

78
00:10:48.692 --> 00:10:50.092
Got it.

79
00:10:50.372 --> 00:10:51.452
Duncan.

80
00:10:51.452 --> 00:10:52.572
<i>My boy.</i>

81
00:10:52.572 --> 00:10:53.972
Hey. Hey.

82
00:10:54.011 --> 00:10:55.491
<i>Paul. my boy.</i>

83
00:10:57.631 --> 00:10:59.991
So. you're going to Arrakis tomorrow.

84
00:11:00.072 --> 00:11:01.472
With the advance team.

85
00:11:01.552 --> 00:11:04.432
Yes. I'm going to Arrakis tomorrow
with the advance team.

86
00:11:05.851 --> 00:11:07.572
I'd like you to take me with you.

87
00:11:08.171 --> 00:11:09.571
You would?

88
00:11:10.292 --> 00:11:11.932
Well. that's too bad. 'Cause no.

89
00:11:13.172 --> 00:11:14.412
Duncan.

90
00:11:14.412 --> 00:11:16.572
Are you trying to get me court-martialed?

91
00:11:17.611 --> 00:11:18.731
What's going on?

92
00:11:18.731 --> 00:11:20.131
Can I trust you with something?

93
00:11:20.172 --> 00:11:21.572
Always. You know that.

94
00:11:28.732 --> 00:11:30.411
I've been having dreams.

95
00:11:32.652 --> 00:11:35.292
About Arrakis and the Fremen.

96
00:11:43.212 --> 00:11:44.892
Okay.

97
00:11:44.971 --> 00:11:46.371
So?

98
00:11:48.031 --> 00:11:49.430
I saw you.

99
00:11:52.352 --> 00:11:54.351
<i>With the Fremen.</i>

100
00:11:54.432 --> 00:11:56.112
Ah.

101
00:11:56.192 --> 00:11:57.592
So. I do find them.

102
00:11:57.631 --> 00:11:59.871
There you go. That's a good
omen right there. right?

103
00:12:03.351 --> 00:12:04.751
Lanville!

104
00:12:10.471 --> 00:12:12.271
I saw you lying dead.

105
00:12:13.152 --> 00:12:14.871
Fallen in battle.

106
00:12:16.111 --> 00:12:20.152
<i>It felt like if I had been there. you'd be alive.</i>

107
00:12:25.551 --> 00:12:27.351
First off. I'm not gonna die.

108
00:12:27.432 --> 00:12:28.631
You're not taking me seriously.

109
00:12:28.631 --> 00:12:30.592
That's why you want to come with me.

110
00:12:30.671 --> 00:12:32.031
Listen.

111
00:12:32.031 --> 00:12:36.031
Dreams make good stories. but everything
important happens when we're awake.

112
00:12:36.111 --> 00:12:38.112
'Cause that's when we make things happen.

113
00:12:38.191 --> 00:12:40.432
Look at you. Put on some muscle?

114
00:12:40.511 --> 00:12:41.751
I did?

115
00:12:41.751 --> 00:12:43.151
No.

116
00:12:45.652 --> 00:12:47.451
Hey.

117
00:12:47.532 --> 00:12:49.612
See you on Arrakis. my boy.

118
00:13:24.992 --> 00:13:29.711
Father. I'd like to ask to join Duncan Idaho
on his scout mission to Arrakis tomorrow.

119
00:13:29.792 --> 00:13:31.631
I've studied the Fremen language. I'd be an asset.

120
00:13:31.712 --> 00:13:32.991
Out of the question.

121
00:13:32.991 --> 00:13:35.471
You'll travel in a few weeks to
Arrakis. like the rest of us.

122
00:13:35.471 --> 00:13:36.792
I've been training my whole life.

123
00:13:36.792 --> 00:13:39.392
What is the point if I'm not allowed
to face some actual risk?

124
00:13:39.392 --> 00:13:40.671
You know why. Paul.

125
00:13:40.671 --> 00:13:42.672
You're the future of house Atreides.

126
00:13:42.751 --> 00:13:45.071
And Grandfather fought bulls for sport!

127
00:13:45.652 --> 00:13:47.292
Yes.

128
00:13:47.371 --> 00:13:48.932
And look where that got him.

129
00:13:53.552 --> 00:13:55.831
I need you by my side.

130
00:13:55.911 --> 00:13:58.831
When we get to Arrakis. we'll
face enormous danger.

131
00:13:58.912 --> 00:14:00.392
What danger?

132
00:14:00.471 --> 00:14:02.271
The Fremen? The desert?

133
00:14:02.352 --> 00:14:04.232
Political danger.

134
00:14:06.652 --> 00:14:11.691
The Great Houses look to us for leadership.
and this threatens the Emperor.

135
00:14:11.771 --> 00:14:14.892
By taking Arrakis from the Harkonnens
and making it ours.

136
00:14:14.971 --> 00:14:19.091
he sets the stage for a war. which
would weaken both houses.

137
00:14:21.071 --> 00:14:27.111
But if we hold firm. and tap the true power
of Arrakis. we could be stronger than ever.

138
00:14:27.192 --> 00:14:28.751
What does that mean?

139
00:14:28.832 --> 00:14:31.432
Mining spice. keeping the Fremen in their place?

140
00:14:31.511 --> 00:14:32.911
We'd be no better than Harkonnens.

141
00:14:33.251 --> 00:14:34.651
No.

142
00:14:34.692 --> 00:14:37.692
By making an alliance with the Fremen.

143
00:14:37.771 --> 00:14:40.371
That's what I've sent Duncan Idaho to arrange.

144
00:14:42.271 --> 00:14:45.831
Here on Caladan. we've ruled
by air power and sea power.

145
00:14:45.911 --> 00:14:49.592
On Arrakis. we need to cultivate desert power.

146
00:14:53.211 --> 00:14:54.931
I want you sitting in on my council.

147
00:14:55.012 --> 00:14:56.411
Learn what I do.

148
00:14:56.412 --> 00:14:58.091
What if I'm not. Dad?

149
00:14:59.651 --> 00:15:01.050
Not what?

150
00:15:02.412 --> 00:15:04.892
The future of house Atreides.

151
00:15:17.651 --> 00:15:20.091
I told my father I didn't want this either.

152
00:15:23.732 --> 00:15:25.652
I wanted to be a pilot.

153
00:15:26.931 --> 00:15:28.331
You never told me that.

154
00:15:31.591 --> 00:15:33.591
Your grandfather said.

155
00:15:33.671 --> 00:15:39.872
“a great man doesn't seek to lead. He's
called to it. and he answers.”

156
00:15:41.971 --> 00:15:43.812
And if your answer is no…

157
00:15:46.771 --> 00:15:49.851
you'll still be the only thing
I ever needed you to be…

158
00:15:51.612 --> 00:15:53.012
my son.

159
00:16:03.531 --> 00:16:07.331
I found my own way to it. Maybe you'll find yours.

160
00:16:10.691 --> 00:16:12.451
In their memory…

161
00:16:14.891 --> 00:16:16.612
give it a try.

162
00:16:26.051 --> 00:16:28.172
Don't stand with your back to the door.

163
00:16:29.331 --> 00:16:30.811
How many times do we have to tell you?

164
00:16:30.891 --> 00:16:34.011
I could tell it was you by your
footsteps. Gurney Halleck.

165
00:16:34.091 --> 00:16:36.731
Someone might imitate my stride.

166
00:16:36.812 --> 00:16:38.091
I know the difference.

167
00:16:38.091 --> 00:16:39.611
Are you the new Weapons Master?

168
00:16:39.692 --> 00:16:43.291
With Duncan Idaho gone. I must
make do as best I can.

169
00:16:44.872 --> 00:16:46.271
Choose your blade.

170
00:16:46.271 --> 00:16:47.951
I've had quite a day. Gurney.

171
00:16:48.031 --> 00:16:49.991
Give us a song instead.

172
00:16:54.391 --> 00:16:55.790
That's rude.

173
00:17:13.231 --> 00:17:14.711
Come on.

174
00:17:14.792 --> 00:17:15.831
Come on.

175
00:17:15.831 --> 00:17:17.231
Old man.

176
00:17:29.191 --> 00:17:31.630
Ah. the slow blade penetrates the shield.

177
00:17:38.932 --> 00:17:40.691
I guess I'm not in the mood today.

178
00:17:40.771 --> 00:17:42.011
- Mood?
- Yeah.

179
00:17:42.011 --> 00:17:43.172
What's mood to do with it?

180
00:17:43.172 --> 00:17:45.971
You fight when the necessity
arises. no matter the mood.

181
00:17:45.971 --> 00:17:47.371
Now. fight!

182
00:17:52.291 --> 00:17:53.691
Come on!

183
00:18:06.451 --> 00:18:08.731
I have you.

184
00:18:08.811 --> 00:18:10.451
Aye.

185
00:18:10.531 --> 00:18:12.131
But look down. my lord.

186
00:18:12.211 --> 00:18:14.691
You'd have joined me in death.

187
00:18:14.771 --> 00:18:16.571
I see you found the mood.

188
00:18:28.291 --> 00:18:29.811
Will it be that bad?

189
00:18:29.892 --> 00:18:32.291
You don't get it. do you?

190
00:18:32.371 --> 00:18:36.212
You don't really understand the grave
nature of what's happening to us.

191
00:18:39.032 --> 00:18:42.592
For eighty years. Arrakis belonged
to House Harkonnen.

192
00:18:42.671 --> 00:18:45.072
Eighty years of owning the spice fields.

193
00:18:45.151 --> 00:18:47.191
Can you imagine the wealth?

194
00:18:47.271 --> 00:18:49.111
Your eyes. I need to see it in your eyes.

195
00:18:49.191 --> 00:18:51.591
You never met Harkonnens before. I have.

196
00:18:51.671 --> 00:18:54.591
They're not human. they're brutal!

197
00:18:54.672 --> 00:18:56.511
You have to be ready.

198
00:19:39.211 --> 00:19:40.611
Lord Baron.

199
00:19:42.292 --> 00:19:44.411
Rabban.

200
00:19:44.491 --> 00:19:47.051
The last of our ships have left Arrakis.

201
00:19:47.891 --> 00:19:49.331
It's done.

202
00:19:49.411 --> 00:19:50.851
Very good.

203
00:19:54.231 --> 00:19:56.232
Uncle. how can we let this happen?

204
00:19:56.311 --> 00:20:03.071
How can the Emperor take everything we've
built and give it to that Duke?

205
00:20:03.151 --> 00:20:04.551
How?

206
00:20:04.971 --> 00:20:07.771
Don't be too sure it's an act of love.

207
00:20:09.891 --> 00:20:11.491
What does he mean?

208
00:20:17.351 --> 00:20:20.071
When is a gift not a gift?

209
00:20:21.751 --> 00:20:28.391
The Atreides' voice is rising. and
the Emperor is a jealous man.

210
00:20:30.971 --> 00:20:33.931
A dangerous. jealous man.

211
00:21:45.651 --> 00:21:47.051
Paul.

212
00:21:48.091 --> 00:21:49.731
Paul. wake up.

213
00:21:55.791 --> 00:21:56.871
What's wrong?

214
00:21:56.871 --> 00:21:59.071
Get dressed and come with me.

215
00:22:19.671 --> 00:22:21.071
What is this?

216
00:22:21.071 --> 00:22:23.871
The Reverend Mother Gaius Helen Mohiam is here.

217
00:22:23.951 --> 00:22:25.991
She was my teacher at the Bene Gesserit school.

218
00:22:26.071 --> 00:22:29.471
She's now Truthsayer to the Emperor himself.

219
00:22:29.551 --> 00:22:31.351
She would like to meet you.

220
00:22:31.911 --> 00:22:33.471
Why?

221
00:22:33.551 --> 00:22:35.791
She wants to know about your dreams.

222
00:22:37.611 --> 00:22:39.371
How does she know about my dreams?

223
00:22:41.931 --> 00:22:43.411
And why is Dr. Yueh here?

224
00:22:43.491 --> 00:22:45.771
He only needs a moment.

225
00:22:46.351 --> 00:22:48.271
Hello. young master.

226
00:22:48.351 --> 00:22:50.951
Your mother asked me to check your vitals.

227
00:22:57.171 --> 00:22:58.571
What's happening?

228
00:23:02.281 --> 00:23:06.091
The Bene Gesserit say they serve
the greater good…

229
00:23:06.372 --> 00:23:08.604
but. meaning no disrespect to
your lady mother…

230
00:23:09.916 --> 00:23:13.725
they also serve their own designs.

231
00:23:15.366 --> 00:23:16.783
What are you saying?

232
00:23:17.384 --> 00:23:18.868
Go carefully.

233
00:23:20.051 --> 00:23:22.811
His heart is strong as ever. my lady.

234
00:23:24.675 --> 00:23:26.727
Tell no one of this.

235
00:23:36.831 --> 00:23:38.231
Paul…

236
00:23:42.314 --> 00:23:45.175
remember your training.

237
00:24:05.371 --> 00:24:10.651
<i>Who are you?</i>

238
00:24:15.851 --> 00:24:18.011
Defiance in the eyes.

239
00:24:18.091 --> 00:24:19.691
Like his father.

240
00:24:19.770 --> 00:24:21.290
Leave us.

241
00:24:21.371 --> 00:24:23.811
You must do everything the
Reverend Mother tells you.

242
00:24:27.711 --> 00:24:29.071
You dismiss my mother in her own house.

243
00:24:29.071 --> 00:24:30.471
[Reverend Mother Using The Voice]
Come here.

244
00:24:30.830 --> 00:24:32.230
[Reverend Mother Using The Voice]
Kneel.

245
00:24:35.751 --> 00:24:37.591
How dare you use The Voice on me?

246
00:24:45.131 --> 00:24:46.531
Put your right hand in the box.

247
00:24:48.451 --> 00:24:50.771
Your mother bade you obey me.

248
00:24:59.531 --> 00:25:01.891
I hold at your neck the Gom Jabbar.

249
00:25:02.891 --> 00:25:04.491
A poison needle.

250
00:25:04.570 --> 00:25:05.970
Instant death.

251
00:25:06.811 --> 00:25:08.291
The test is simple.

252
00:25:08.371 --> 00:25:12.411
Remove your hand from the box and you die.

253
00:25:13.330 --> 00:25:15.011
What's in the box?

254
00:25:16.210 --> 00:25:17.610
Pain.

255
00:25:19.771 --> 00:25:22.850
No need to call the guards.

256
00:25:22.931 --> 00:25:24.490
<i>Your mother stands behind that door.</i>

257
00:25:24.571 --> 00:25:26.211
<i>No one would get past her.</i>

258
00:25:32.891 --> 00:25:34.331
<i>Why are you doing this?</i>

259
00:25:36.010 --> 00:25:40.051
An animal caught in a trap will
gnaw off its own leg to escape.

260
00:25:40.731 --> 00:25:42.131
What will you do?

261
00:26:15.071 --> 00:26:17.111
Silence.

262
00:26:25.591 --> 00:26:27.350
I must not fear.

263
00:26:29.031 --> 00:26:30.551
I must not fear.

264
00:26:37.211 --> 00:26:39.011
Fear is the mind-killer.

265
00:26:41.010 --> 00:26:42.291
<i>Fear</i>

266
00:26:42.291 --> 00:26:44.570
is the little death that brings obliteration.

267
00:26:47.251 --> 00:26:50.411
And I'll face my fear and I'll permit
it to pass over me and through me.

268
00:27:05.850 --> 00:27:07.250
And when it has gone past…

269
00:27:15.950 --> 00:27:18.710
I will turn the inner eye and see its path.

270
00:27:23.131 --> 00:27:27.930
And where the fear has gone.
there will be nothing.

271
00:27:31.331 --> 00:27:32.770
Only I will remain.

272
00:27:36.930 --> 00:27:38.330
Enough.

273
00:27:55.511 --> 00:28:00.591
Like sifting sand through
a screen. we sift people.

274
00:28:00.671 --> 00:28:07.230
If you had been unable to control your impulses.
like an animal. we could not let you live.

275
00:28:07.311 --> 00:28:09.871
You inherit too much power.

276
00:28:09.950 --> 00:28:13.790
- What. because I'm a duke's son?
- Because you are Jessica's son.

277
00:28:13.871 --> 00:28:16.390
You have more than one birthright. boy.

278
00:28:18.451 --> 00:28:19.851
Jessica?

279
00:28:26.210 --> 00:28:28.451
You've been training him in the way.

280
00:28:33.190 --> 00:28:35.750
Tell me about these dreams.

281
00:28:35.831 --> 00:28:37.871
- I had one tonight.
- What did you see?

282
00:28:40.671 --> 00:28:42.070
A girl.

283
00:28:42.070 --> 00:28:43.671
On Arrakis.

284
00:28:43.750 --> 00:28:45.150
Have you dreamt of her before?

285
00:28:49.531 --> 00:28:50.931
Many times.

286
00:28:53.371 --> 00:28:56.811
Do you often dream things that happen
just as you dreamed them?

287
00:29:00.311 --> 00:29:01.711
Not exactly.

288
00:29:05.030 --> 00:29:06.591
Goodbye. young human.

289
00:29:07.350 --> 00:29:08.911
I hope you live.

290
00:29:17.430 --> 00:29:19.431
Did you have to go that far?

291
00:29:19.511 --> 00:29:23.111
You chose to train him in the
way. in defiance of our rule.

292
00:29:23.190 --> 00:29:24.670
He wields our power.

293
00:29:24.751 --> 00:29:27.430
He had to be tested to the limits.

294
00:29:27.511 --> 00:29:30.631
So. much potential. wasted in a male.

295
00:29:30.710 --> 00:29:34.070
You were told to bear only daughters.
but you. in your pride.

296
00:29:34.071 --> 00:29:35.991
thought you could produce the <i>Kwisatz Haderach.</i>

297
00:29:36.991 --> 00:29:38.391
Was I wrong?

298
00:29:38.430 --> 00:29:41.070
You're lucky he didn't die in that room.

299
00:29:41.150 --> 00:29:43.311
If he is the one. he has a long way to go.

300
00:29:43.390 --> 00:29:46.311
His sight is barely awakened. and
now he goes into the fire.

301
00:29:47.711 --> 00:29:50.070
but our Plans Are measured in centuries.

302
00:29:50.151 --> 00:29:53.991
We have other prospects if he fails his promise.

303
00:29:56.971 --> 00:29:59.370
Do you see so little hope?

304
00:29:59.451 --> 00:30:02.410
On Arrakis. we have done all we can for you.

305
00:30:02.491 --> 00:30:04.251
A path has been laid.

306
00:30:04.330 --> 00:30:06.490
Let's hope he doesn't squander it.

307
00:30:54.311 --> 00:30:55.711
Paul.

308
00:30:56.430 --> 00:30:57.950
What does it mean?

309
00:30:59.271 --> 00:31:00.870
That I could be the one?

310
00:31:00.950 --> 00:31:02.350
You heard.

311
00:31:05.471 --> 00:31:11.550
The Bene Gesserit serve as powerful partners
to the Great Houses. but there's more to it.

312
00:31:11.930 --> 00:31:15.851
You steer the politics of the
Imperium from the shadows.

313
00:31:16.491 --> 00:31:17.530
I know.

314
00:31:17.530 --> 00:31:19.890
You don't know everything.

315
00:31:20.470 --> 00:31:25.270
For thousands of years. we've been
carefully crossings bloodlines

316
00:31:25.351 --> 00:31:27.390
- to bring forth—
- The one?

317
00:31:28.511 --> 00:31:36.250
A mind… powerful enough
to bridge space and time.

318
00:31:37.010 --> 00:31:38.771
Past and future.

319
00:31:41.191 --> 00:31:43.391
Who can help us into a better future.

320
00:31:44.550 --> 00:31:47.110
We think he's very close now.

321
00:31:48.991 --> 00:31:51.071
Some believe he's here.

322
00:31:54.911 --> 00:31:56.831
All part of a plan.

323
00:34:15.310 --> 00:34:16.711
Shield.

324
00:34:58.990 --> 00:35:02.790
“My lungs taste the air of time.
blown past falling sand…”

325
00:35:47.631 --> 00:35:49.031
Thufir Hawat.

326
00:35:53.030 --> 00:35:54.430
Young master!

327
00:35:55.010 --> 00:35:57.210
How does it feel to walk on a new world?

328
00:35:57.290 --> 00:35:59.130
Exciting. to say the least.

329
00:35:59.810 --> 00:36:01.571
My lord.

330
00:36:01.650 --> 00:36:03.210
How are you. old friend?

331
00:36:03.290 --> 00:36:05.530
My advance team has secured the city.

332
00:36:05.610 --> 00:36:08.490
We're still smoothing out a few rough spots.

333
00:36:10.550 --> 00:36:11.950
My lady.

334
00:36:16.110 --> 00:36:17.991
<i>Lisan al-Gaib!</i>

335
00:36:33.610 --> 00:36:36.490
<i>Lisan al-Gaib! Lisan al-Gaib!</i>

336
00:36:37.530 --> 00:36:39.450
<i>Lisan al-Gaib!</i>

337
00:36:39.530 --> 00:36:41.690
<i>Lisan al-Gaib! Lisan al-Gaib!</i>

338
00:36:41.770 --> 00:36:44.610
<i>Lisan al-Gaib! Lisan al-Gaib!</i>

339
00:36:44.690 --> 00:36:47.490
<i>Lisan al-Gaib! Lisan al-Gaib!</i>

340
00:36:47.570 --> 00:36:50.450
<i>Lisan al-Gaib! Lisan al-Gaib!</i>

341
00:36:53.591 --> 00:36:55.270
Don't be fooled by the welcome.

342
00:36:55.350 --> 00:36:57.151
They follow their old masters' rules.

343
00:36:57.230 --> 00:36:58.391
Mandatory attendance.

344
00:36:58.391 --> 00:37:00.590
That's Harkonnen love out there.

345
00:37:06.990 --> 00:37:08.390
Atreides!

346
00:37:08.430 --> 00:37:11.870
Atreides! Atreides! Atreides!

347
00:37:11.950 --> 00:37:15.550
Atreides! Atreides! Atreides!

348
00:37:15.630 --> 00:37:17.990
Atreides! Atreides!

349
00:37:21.030 --> 00:37:23.670
Let's get you out of the sun.

350
00:37:23.750 --> 00:37:26.150
The heat can kill in this place.

351
00:37:42.710 --> 00:37:44.390
They were pointing at us.

352
00:37:45.350 --> 00:37:46.710
What are they shouting?

353
00:37:46.710 --> 00:37:50.470
<i>Lisan al-Gaib.</i> “Voice from the outer world.”

354
00:37:50.550 --> 00:37:53.150
It's their name for “messiah.”

355
00:37:53.230 --> 00:37:56.390
It means the Bene Gesserit have been at work here.

356
00:37:56.470 --> 00:37:58.830
Planting superstitions.

357
00:37:58.910 --> 00:38:01.590
Preparing the way. Paul.

358
00:38:01.670 --> 00:38:05.670
These people have waited for centuries for the <i>Lisan al-Gaib.</i>

359
00:38:06.850 --> 00:38:10.530
They see you. they see the signs.

360
00:38:13.510 --> 00:38:15.870
They see what they've been told to see.

361
00:38:20.750 --> 00:38:22.150
We're good to go.

362
00:39:05.470 --> 00:39:06.830
Shield wall.

363
00:39:06.830 --> 00:39:10.150
Protects the city from the weather and the worms.

364
00:39:57.070 --> 00:39:59.790
The locals call the big one the hand of God.

365
00:40:01.510 --> 00:40:05.550
Well. the hand of God is wreaking
havoc on our comms system.

366
00:40:09.130 --> 00:40:10.530
It's so quiet.

367
00:40:11.530 --> 00:40:13.490
Yeah.

368
00:40:13.570 --> 00:40:15.370
That's what worries me. too.

369
00:40:22.850 --> 00:40:27.129
There's the spaceport and that plume
of dust there is the spice refinery.

370
00:40:27.210 --> 00:40:29.210
Our two most vulnerable points.

371
00:40:29.290 --> 00:40:30.610
I want you guarding them.

372
00:40:30.610 --> 00:40:33.130
If we can't refine spice and ship it off-world.

373
00:40:33.210 --> 00:40:35.170
- we're dead here.
- My lord.

374
00:40:35.250 --> 00:40:37.770
The sun's getting too high.
We need to seal the doors.

375
00:40:41.890 --> 00:40:44.370
What do they say about this hellhole again?

376
00:40:45.450 --> 00:40:47.810
“To shower. you scrub your ass
with sand. ” my lord.

377
00:40:47.890 --> 00:40:49.370
That's what they say.

378
00:40:49.450 --> 00:40:51.010
That's what they say.

379
00:40:55.370 --> 00:40:57.970
Candidates for a housekeeper. my lady.

380
00:41:14.090 --> 00:41:15.530
What is your name?

381
00:41:15.610 --> 00:41:17.689
Shadout Mapes. my lady.

382
00:41:19.370 --> 00:41:21.370
The rest of you may go.

383
00:41:21.450 --> 00:41:22.850
Thank you.

384
00:41:24.730 --> 00:41:26.610
Shadout.

385
00:41:26.690 --> 00:41:28.410
It's an old Chakobsa word.

386
00:41:29.130 --> 00:41:30.530
“Well-dipper.”

387
00:41:33.370 --> 00:41:34.610
You know the ancient tongues?

388
00:41:34.610 --> 00:41:36.010
I know many things.

389
00:41:36.590 --> 00:41:39.630
I know that you have a weapon
concealed in your bodice.

390
00:41:40.700 --> 00:41:43.230
- Not now.
- If you mean to harm me.

391
00:41:43.310 --> 00:41:48.190
I must warn you. whatever you're
hiding. it won't be enough.

392
00:41:50.369 --> 00:41:55.770
The weapon is meant as a gift
if you are truly the one.

393
00:42:12.429 --> 00:42:13.990
Do you know this?

394
00:42:15.270 --> 00:42:16.829
It's a crysknife.

395
00:42:20.470 --> 00:42:21.870
Do you know its meaning?

396
00:42:22.478 --> 00:42:24.501
Be ready for violence.

397
00:42:25.869 --> 00:42:27.430
It's a Maker—

398
00:42:33.309 --> 00:42:35.670
A Maker of the deep desert.

399
00:42:38.109 --> 00:42:42.990
When you have lived with prophecy for so long.
the moment of revelation is a shock.

400
00:42:43.069 --> 00:42:44.670
<i>Lisan al-Gaib.</i>

401
00:42:44.750 --> 00:42:46.790
The mother and the son.

402
00:42:52.970 --> 00:42:54.650
It is yours.

403
00:42:56.169 --> 00:42:59.650
Tooth of <i>Shai-Hulud.</i>

404
00:43:29.529 --> 00:43:32.210
<i>Lisan! Lisan al-Gaib!</i>

405
00:43:32.289 --> 00:43:41.500
<i>Lisan al-Gaib! Lisan al-Gaib!</i>

406
00:43:47.170 --> 00:43:48.570
Hello.

407
00:43:50.610 --> 00:43:53.210
You shouldn't be out here at this hour of the day.

408
00:43:55.290 --> 00:43:57.450
They're out here.

409
00:43:57.530 --> 00:44:00.049
Hmm. Fremen pilgrims.

410
00:44:00.130 --> 00:44:02.010
They don't care about heatstroke.

411
00:44:04.650 --> 00:44:07.769
I didn't know date palms could
even be found out here.

412
00:44:07.850 --> 00:44:10.850
Oh. these aren't indigenous.

413
00:44:10.929 --> 00:44:13.290
They can't survive without me.

414
00:44:13.369 --> 00:44:17.089
Each one of these drinks every day
the equivalent of five men.

415
00:44:19.629 --> 00:44:21.230
Twenty palm trees.

416
00:44:22.470 --> 00:44:24.910
A hundred lives.

417
00:44:24.989 --> 00:44:26.950
Should we remove them? Save the water?

418
00:44:27.029 --> 00:44:28.429
No. no. no.

419
00:44:28.470 --> 00:44:29.990
These are sacred.

420
00:44:34.689 --> 00:44:36.090
Old dream.

421
00:44:44.150 --> 00:44:49.149
<i>The largest and most dangerous organism
on Arrakis is the sandworm.</i>

422
00:44:49.230 --> 00:44:53.190
<i>capable of reaching four hundred meters in length.</i>

423
00:44:53.769 --> 00:44:57.570
<i>To avoid making rhythmic noises.
which attract the sandworms.</i>

424
00:44:57.650 --> 00:45:04.410
<i>the Fremen cross desert spaces using the sandwalk. a dance-like motion with irregular rhythm</i>

425
00:45:04.489 --> 00:45:08.329
<i>which emulates the natural sounds of the desert.</i>

426
00:45:08.910 --> 00:45:13.030
<i>What scant plant life exists on Arrakis
is thanks to the Fremen.</i>

427
00:45:13.110 --> 00:45:15.910
<i>who have cultivated deep-rooted terranic plants</i>

428
00:45:15.990 --> 00:45:22.910
<i>such as saguaro. burrobush. sand-verbena and incense bush.</i>

429
00:45:23.490 --> 00:45:26.609
<i>The shepherd's tree has the
deepest documented roots.</i>

430
00:45:26.690 --> 00:45:31.009
<i>stretching more than four hundred
and fifty feet deep.</i>

431
00:45:31.090 --> 00:45:36.130
<i>These plants cling to life in a parched. nutrient-poor landscape.</i>

432
00:46:46.909 --> 00:46:48.549
It's a hunter-seeker.

433
00:46:48.630 --> 00:46:50.589
The operator must be nearby.

434
00:46:55.929 --> 00:46:59.209
<i>The Harkonnen agent was cemented
into that hole six weeks ago.</i>

435
00:46:59.290 --> 00:47:02.409
<i>Ran the hunter-seeker through a water pipe inside the walls.</i>

436
00:47:03.289 --> 00:47:06.250
Sire. I failed you today. There's no excuse.

437
00:47:06.329 --> 00:47:07.729
You have my resignation.

438
00:47:07.770 --> 00:47:09.089
You would deprive us of your talents at this time?

439
00:47:09.089 --> 00:47:10.329
Sire. my honor demands—

440
00:47:10.329 --> 00:47:11.969
They tried to take the life of my son!

441
00:47:13.590 --> 00:47:14.990
I don't give a damn about your honor.

442
00:47:15.069 --> 00:47:17.549
You want absolution? Go catch some spies.

443
00:47:17.630 --> 00:47:19.030
Your Grace.

444
00:47:26.789 --> 00:47:28.949
The thing must leave.

445
00:47:29.030 --> 00:47:31.429
You can speak without fear.

446
00:47:31.510 --> 00:47:33.710
Our pet doesn't understand your language.

447
00:47:33.789 --> 00:47:35.190
Get out.

448
00:47:39.389 --> 00:47:41.110
It understands.

449
00:47:41.189 --> 00:47:42.669
Activate silence.

450
00:47:47.257 --> 00:47:49.946
What is the Emperor's message?

451
00:47:50.302 --> 00:47:53.040
He will strengthen your hand.

452
00:47:55.679 --> 00:47:57.845
With his Sardaukar Army.

453
00:47:57.930 --> 00:48:00.329
It must never be known.

454
00:48:00.410 --> 00:48:03.209
There's no satellites over Arrakis.

455
00:48:03.290 --> 00:48:06.769
The Atreides will die in the dark.

456
00:48:06.850 --> 00:48:11.569
On that matter. Duke Leto Atreides
means nothing to our order.

457
00:48:12.150 --> 00:48:16.630
but his wife is under our protection
and by extension. her son.

458
00:48:17.209 --> 00:48:19.610
Allow them the dignity of exile.

459
00:48:23.610 --> 00:48:28.369
House Harkonnen would never dream of violating
the sanctity of your order.

460
00:48:29.370 --> 00:48:30.969
I give you my word.

461
00:48:31.049 --> 00:48:32.650
We will not harm them.

462
00:48:53.549 --> 00:48:55.029
If the Duke's son lives—

463
00:48:55.109 --> 00:48:57.509
No Atreides will live.

464
00:48:57.590 --> 00:48:59.909
My lord. you gave your word to the witch.

465
00:48:59.989 --> 00:49:01.109
She sees too much.

466
00:49:01.109 --> 00:49:04.149
I said I would not harm them. and I shall not.

467
00:49:04.149 --> 00:49:09.989
But Arrakis is Arrakis. and
the desert takes the weak.

468
00:49:12.490 --> 00:49:13.890
My desert.

469
00:49:16.409 --> 00:49:18.290
My Arrakis.

470
00:49:20.129 --> 00:49:21.729
My Dune.

471
00:49:25.809 --> 00:49:28.050
Your first strategy meeting.

472
00:49:28.129 --> 00:49:32.689
Paul Atreides. who catches hunter-seekers in his bare hands like a hero of old.

473
00:49:34.689 --> 00:49:36.769
Thanks for the humiliation. old man.

474
00:49:36.849 --> 00:49:38.249
Gotta keep an eye on you.

475
00:49:38.929 --> 00:49:40.329
Attention!

476
00:49:48.849 --> 00:49:50.249
Let's get started.

477
00:49:52.490 --> 00:49:54.249
Thufir. Operations.

478
00:49:54.329 --> 00:49:56.890
I secured a copy of the Harkonnens' account books.

479
00:49:59.749 --> 00:50:04.390
The Harkonnens were taking ten billion
solaris out of here every year.

480
00:50:04.469 --> 00:50:08.549
“They shall suck of the abundance of the
seas. and the treasure hid in the sand.”

481
00:50:08.630 --> 00:50:10.909
We won't see profits like that for a while.

482
00:50:11.489 --> 00:50:13.569
Not with the equipment they left us.

483
00:50:14.490 --> 00:50:16.049
How bad is it?

484
00:50:22.029 --> 00:50:23.949
These are spice silos.

485
00:50:25.270 --> 00:50:28.229
We're meant to fill every crate.

486
00:50:28.309 --> 00:50:30.149
All of them?

487
00:50:30.229 --> 00:50:32.950
Every twenty-five standard days.

488
00:50:33.029 --> 00:50:35.270
Harkonnen sabotage slows us down.

489
00:50:35.349 --> 00:50:36.989
But who's meant to arbitrate?

490
00:50:37.070 --> 00:50:39.710
Isn't there a Judge of the Change
to oversee the transition?

491
00:50:40.129 --> 00:50:41.529
Who did the Emperor appoint?

492
00:50:41.569 --> 00:50:44.249
Dr. Liet Kynes. Imperial Ecologist.

493
00:50:44.329 --> 00:50:45.769
Been here twenty years.

494
00:50:45.849 --> 00:50:47.609
Eccentric. from what I'm told.

495
00:50:47.689 --> 00:50:50.610
I want to see these harvesting fields myself.

496
00:50:50.689 --> 00:50:52.089
I wouldn't recommend it. my lord.

497
00:50:52.590 --> 00:50:54.950
Have this Judge of the Change accompany us.

498
00:50:55.029 --> 00:50:58.630
A meeting's long overdue. and we'll
get a bit of Imperial protection.

499
00:50:59.209 --> 00:51:00.650
A hostage.

500
00:51:00.729 --> 00:51:02.049
I love it.

501
00:51:02.049 --> 00:51:03.169
Hmm.

502
00:51:03.169 --> 00:51:05.329
He's here. my lord.

503
00:51:29.289 --> 00:51:31.169
Take care of them. They are friends.

504
00:51:31.249 --> 00:51:32.249
Duncan!

505
00:51:32.249 --> 00:51:33.649
Ah! My boy!

506
00:51:39.629 --> 00:51:40.830
I swear you're getting taller.

507
00:51:40.830 --> 00:51:42.429
Well. you smell much worse.

508
00:51:45.989 --> 00:51:47.869
For four weeks. I lived with the Fremen.

509
00:51:47.950 --> 00:51:50.710
Hidden in the desert. in a community
called a <i>Sietch.</i>

510
00:51:50.789 --> 00:51:53.829
Stilgar. the leader of that <i>Sietch.</i>
has come with me to meet you. sire.

511
00:51:54.409 --> 00:51:56.649
This <i>Sietch.</i> how is it hidden?

512
00:51:56.729 --> 00:51:57.849
It's underground.

513
00:51:57.849 --> 00:51:59.729
Arrakis is filled with caverns.

514
00:51:59.809 --> 00:52:01.409
How big was the place?

515
00:52:01.990 --> 00:52:05.909
I'd say ten thousand people. and there
are hundreds of <i>sietches.</i>

516
00:52:07.070 --> 00:52:08.470
Millions of Fremen.

517
00:52:09.189 --> 00:52:10.589
You were right.

518
00:52:10.669 --> 00:52:13.869
The Harkonnen estimate was fifty
thousand on the whole planet.

519
00:52:14.449 --> 00:52:16.569
The Fremen watched me search for them for days.

520
00:52:16.649 --> 00:52:18.049
I never saw them.

521
00:52:18.130 --> 00:52:20.730
Finally. they sent a warrior out to kill me.

522
00:52:20.809 --> 00:52:22.329
And I gotta tell you.

523
00:52:22.409 --> 00:52:24.729
I have never come so close to dying.

524
00:52:24.809 --> 00:52:27.489
There's no finer fighter in the Imperium.

525
00:52:27.569 --> 00:52:29.090
They fight like demons.

526
00:52:29.169 --> 00:52:30.969
Desert power.

527
00:52:33.789 --> 00:52:35.469
Duncan.

528
00:52:35.549 --> 00:52:36.949
- Well done.
- Thank you. my lord.

529
00:52:37.029 --> 00:52:38.429
Sire.

530
00:52:38.429 --> 00:52:40.909
Their leader has a knife he
won't surrender. sire.

531
00:52:40.989 --> 00:52:43.949
It's a crysknife. It's sacred to his people.

532
00:52:44.029 --> 00:52:45.429
Let him pass.

533
00:53:02.149 --> 00:53:03.549
Stop there.

534
00:53:03.549 --> 00:53:05.150
Hey! Hey!

535
00:53:09.090 --> 00:53:10.490
Mm.

536
00:53:10.809 --> 00:53:12.209
Stilgar.

537
00:53:12.889 --> 00:53:14.289
Welcome.

538
00:53:15.169 --> 00:53:19.249
Sir. I respect the personal dignity
of any man that respects mine.

539
00:53:22.409 --> 00:53:23.809
Hmm.

540
00:53:27.809 --> 00:53:29.209
Hold.

541
00:53:30.169 --> 00:53:35.369
Thank you. Stilgar. for the gift
of your body's moisture.

542
00:53:35.450 --> 00:53:37.689
We accept it in the spirit in which it was given.

543
00:53:45.869 --> 00:53:47.269
I'm glad you've come.

544
00:53:47.829 --> 00:53:51.149
I believe your people and mine have
much to offer one another.

545
00:53:51.569 --> 00:53:52.969
No. no. you are Outworlders.

546
00:53:52.969 --> 00:53:57.009
You come here for the spice. you take
it. giving nothing in return.

547
00:53:58.689 --> 00:54:00.089
That's true.

548
00:54:01.529 --> 00:54:04.329
I know you've suffered at the
hands of the Harkonnen.

549
00:54:05.449 --> 00:54:06.849
Name what you want.

550
00:54:06.929 --> 00:54:09.569
If it's in my power to grant. I'll
give it and ask for nothing.

551
00:54:10.150 --> 00:54:12.909
Mm. I ask for this. Do not seek our <i>sietches.</i>

552
00:54:12.989 --> 00:54:15.709
Do not trespass in our lands.

553
00:54:16.289 --> 00:54:19.609
The desert was ours <i>long</i> before you came.

554
00:54:19.689 --> 00:54:22.729
So. come and dig your spice. but when you have it.

555
00:54:22.729 --> 00:54:26.569
go back to this side of the shield wall
and leave the desert to the Fremen.

556
00:54:26.649 --> 00:54:29.329
You will address the Duke as “my
lord” or “sire.”

557
00:54:29.409 --> 00:54:31.889
Gurney. just… just a moment.

558
00:54:31.969 --> 00:54:37.729
The Emperor has given me Arrakis
as my fief to rule and protect.

559
00:54:38.309 --> 00:54:43.509
I cannot promise not to travel into
the desert if duty compels me.

560
00:54:43.589 --> 00:54:49.449
but your <i>sietches</i> will be yours forever. and
you will never be hunted while I govern here.

561
00:54:53.769 --> 00:54:55.529
That's very honorable.

562
00:54:56.109 --> 00:54:58.669
I must go. That's all I have to say to you.

563
00:54:58.749 --> 00:55:00.829
Won't you stay?

564
00:55:00.909 --> 00:55:02.309
We would honor you.

565
00:55:02.309 --> 00:55:05.269
Honor requires that I be elsewhere.

566
00:55:07.078 --> 00:55:09.407
I recognize you.

567
00:55:16.969 --> 00:55:18.249
I don't like him.

568
00:55:18.249 --> 00:55:20.409
Our plan bears fruit.

569
00:55:20.489 --> 00:55:21.889
But it will take time?

570
00:55:22.429 --> 00:55:23.829
Yes.

571
00:55:24.549 --> 00:55:26.749
It will take time.

572
00:55:29.889 --> 00:55:31.289
Here. this is for you.

573
00:55:35.129 --> 00:55:37.049
It's a paracompass.

574
00:55:37.129 --> 00:55:42.129
The moons here have a magnetic field. so…
a simple compass needle won't point north.

575
00:55:42.209 --> 00:55:44.249
Takes a clever piece of clockwork to sort it out.

576
00:55:44.329 --> 00:55:45.929
The Fremen make these?

577
00:55:46.009 --> 00:55:49.249
And stillsuits. and sand compactors.
and all kinds of ingenious things.

578
00:55:49.789 --> 00:55:51.669
What the hell is a sand compactor?

579
00:55:53.789 --> 00:55:55.189
That's a sand compactor.

580
00:55:56.029 --> 00:55:58.669
My God. man. you've gone native.

581
00:55:58.749 --> 00:56:00.149
You admire them.

582
00:56:01.729 --> 00:56:03.169
I do.

583
00:56:03.249 --> 00:56:05.809
They're fierce. but loyal.

584
00:56:05.889 --> 00:56:07.609
They're attuned to the desert.

585
00:56:07.689 --> 00:56:08.969
Part of it.

586
00:56:08.969 --> 00:56:11.009
It's part of them.

587
00:56:11.589 --> 00:56:12.989
You wait till you see it.

588
00:56:13.509 --> 00:56:14.909
It's beautiful out there.

589
00:56:17.989 --> 00:56:19.949
<i>Sunrise warning. all workers.</i>

590
00:56:20.029 --> 00:56:22.869
<i>Temperature today will reach one
hundred and forty degrees.</i>

591
00:56:22.949 --> 00:56:24.629
<i>We are currently ninety degrees.</i>

592
00:56:24.709 --> 00:56:27.949
<i>and in ten minutes. we will hit one
hundred and twenty degrees.</i>

593
00:56:28.989 --> 00:56:30.389
<i>Last warning call.</i>

594
00:57:04.149 --> 00:57:06.229
The Judge of the Change. sire.

595
00:57:06.309 --> 00:57:08.189
Dr. Liet Kynes.

596
00:57:08.269 --> 00:57:09.669
My lord Duke.

597
00:57:10.389 --> 00:57:11.909
Welcome to Arrakis.

598
00:57:12.489 --> 00:57:14.489
You're the Imperial Ecologist.

599
00:57:14.568 --> 00:57:16.409
Thank you for the stillsuits.

600
00:57:16.488 --> 00:57:18.489
They are of Fremen make.

601
00:57:19.069 --> 00:57:20.189
The best.

602
00:57:20.189 --> 00:57:22.909
With your permission. sire. I must check
the integrity of your suit—

603
00:57:22.909 --> 00:57:24.309
Whoa.

604
00:57:24.668 --> 00:57:26.068
It's all right.

605
00:57:27.389 --> 00:57:29.509
It's all right.

606
00:57:29.589 --> 00:57:33.029
Dr. Kynes. we're in your hands.

607
00:57:37.889 --> 00:57:42.889
A stillsuit is a high-efficiency filtration system.

608
00:57:42.969 --> 00:57:44.489
Even this early in the morning.

609
00:57:44.569 --> 00:57:47.248
you wouldn't survive two hours
without one of these.

610
00:57:48.629 --> 00:57:54.549
It cools the body and recycles
the water lost to sweat.

611
00:57:54.629 --> 00:57:57.789
Your body's movements provide the power.

612
00:57:57.869 --> 00:58:01.589
Inside the mask. you'll find a tube to
allow you to drink the recycled water.

613
00:58:02.169 --> 00:58:03.449
Mm.

614
00:58:03.449 --> 00:58:07.009
In good working order. your suit won't lose
more than a thimbleful of water a day.

615
00:58:07.089 --> 00:58:08.489
Most impressive.

616
00:58:10.009 --> 00:58:11.409
Let's have a look at you. lad.

617
00:58:13.529 --> 00:58:16.209
You've… worn a stillsuit before?

618
00:58:16.209 --> 00:58:17.769
No. this is my first time.

619
00:58:20.889 --> 00:58:23.408
Your desert boots are fitted slip-fashion at the ankles.

620
00:58:23.489 --> 00:58:25.249
Who taught you to do that?

621
00:58:25.328 --> 00:58:27.289
It seemed the right way.

622
00:58:30.189 --> 00:58:33.183
He shall know your ways as though born to them.

623
00:58:34.888 --> 00:58:36.288
Are you Fremen?

624
00:58:37.909 --> 00:58:41.669
I am accepted in both <i>Sietch</i> and village.

625
00:58:41.749 --> 00:58:47.309
Now. come and see the spice sands
on which your livelihood depends.

626
00:59:26.008 --> 00:59:28.729
What would you do if your ornithopter
went down out here?

627
00:59:28.809 --> 00:59:30.849
You wouldn't want to go down out there.

628
00:59:30.928 --> 00:59:32.448
It's worm territory.

629
00:59:34.969 --> 00:59:36.369
Dust cloud.

630
00:59:37.049 --> 00:59:39.168
I see it.

631
00:59:39.249 --> 00:59:41.289
That's one of your harvesters.

632
01:00:07.869 --> 01:00:10.869
You can see the spice scattered over the surface.

633
01:00:12.309 --> 01:00:15.709
A rich spice bed by the color.

634
01:00:15.789 --> 01:00:18.188
If you get a little higher.
you'll have a better view.

635
01:00:33.308 --> 01:00:35.829
You see these spotter aircraft
looking for wormsign.

636
01:00:37.789 --> 01:00:39.029
Wormsign?

637
01:00:39.029 --> 01:00:41.229
A sand wave moving toward the crawler.

638
01:00:41.309 --> 01:00:44.909
Worms travel deep but get closer
to the surface when they attack.

639
01:00:46.089 --> 01:00:50.369
If you are patient. we should see one.

640
01:00:50.449 --> 01:00:51.849
A worm always comes?

641
01:00:51.929 --> 01:00:54.609
Always. They're drawn by rhythmic noises.

642
01:00:55.189 --> 01:00:57.188
Why don't we just shield the crawlers?

643
01:00:57.269 --> 01:00:59.668
A shield's a death sentence in the desert.

644
01:00:59.749 --> 01:01:03.589
It attracts the worms and drives
them into a killing frenzy.

645
01:01:06.229 --> 01:01:07.629
Is that a worm?

646
01:01:19.449 --> 01:01:21.168
Big one.

647
01:01:21.249 --> 01:01:23.488
You have good eyes.

648
01:01:23.569 --> 01:01:25.729
Calling crawler Delta Ajax niner.

649
01:01:25.808 --> 01:01:28.209
Wormsign warning. Acknowledge.

650
01:01:28.788 --> 01:01:31.388
<i>Who calls Delta Ajax niner?</i>

651
01:01:31.469 --> 01:01:32.549
<i>Over.</i>

652
01:01:32.549 --> 01:01:33.949
They seem pretty calm about it.

653
01:01:33.988 --> 01:01:36.389
Unlisted flight. Imperium business.

654
01:01:36.468 --> 01:01:38.548
Wormsign north and east of you.

655
01:01:38.629 --> 01:01:40.549
Three point seven kilometers.

656
01:01:41.129 --> 01:01:44.409
<i>Delta Ajax niner. this is Spotter
One. Wormsign confirmed.</i>

657
01:01:45.728 --> 01:01:47.928
<i>Stand by for contact fix.</i>

658
01:01:51.829 --> 01:01:54.309
<i>Worm is on intercept course to your position.</i>

659
01:01:54.389 --> 01:01:55.909
<i>Contact in five minutes.</i>

660
01:01:55.988 --> 01:01:57.709
So. what happens now?

661
01:01:58.288 --> 01:02:00.728
They'll call a carryall to lift the crawler.

662
01:02:00.809 --> 01:02:02.849
They'll harvest right up to the last minute.

663
01:02:02.928 --> 01:02:04.489
<i>Calling carryall Alpha zero.</i>

664
01:02:04.568 --> 01:02:06.329
<i>Ready for docking sequence.</i>

665
01:02:06.409 --> 01:02:08.769
<i>Contact five minutes. Over.</i>

666
01:02:12.968 --> 01:02:15.008
<i>Anybody got a visual on the carryall?</i>

667
01:02:19.549 --> 01:02:20.988
There it is.

668
01:02:21.069 --> 01:02:22.429
<i>This is carryall Alpha zero</i>

669
01:02:22.429 --> 01:02:24.668
<i>to Delta Ajax niner.</i>

670
01:02:24.749 --> 01:02:26.709
<i>Approaching from your east.</i>

671
01:02:27.289 --> 01:02:30.049
<i>Correcting altitude and preparing
docking equipment.</i>

672
01:02:30.128 --> 01:02:33.489
<i>Copy. Alpha zero. Initiating docking sequence.</i>

673
01:02:35.449 --> 01:02:36.889
<i>T-5.</i>

674
01:02:36.968 --> 01:02:38.368
<i>Copy that.</i>

675
01:02:38.449 --> 01:02:40.128
<i>Prepare to be airborne in thirty seconds.</i>

676
01:02:40.209 --> 01:02:42.409
<i>Docking sequence initiated. Brace yourselves.</i>

677
01:02:46.148 --> 01:02:48.109
<i>Alpha zero. we're short one point of contact.</i>

678
01:02:48.188 --> 01:02:49.589
<i>What is going on?</i>

679
01:02:49.668 --> 01:02:51.588
<i>It's one of the anchors. It's dead.</i>

680
01:02:53.048 --> 01:02:54.448
Shit.

681
01:02:54.448 --> 01:02:56.409
<i>Carryall unable to receive.</i>

682
01:02:56.488 --> 01:02:58.288
<i>Unable to lift without that anchor.</i>

683
01:02:58.369 --> 01:03:00.009
<i>All call! All call!</i>

684
01:03:00.088 --> 01:03:02.928
<i>Any carryall in the sector. please respond!</i>

685
01:03:03.509 --> 01:03:05.369
<i>Spotter One. give us an update. Over.</i>

686
01:03:05.369 --> 01:03:06.749
<i>Hydraulics are dead.</i>

687
01:03:06.749 --> 01:03:08.247
<i>We won't make it. You have to evacuate.</i>

688
01:03:08.247 --> 01:03:09.169
<i>Contact in four minutes.</i>

689
01:03:09.169 --> 01:03:10.169
<i>Try it again!</i>

690
01:03:10.169 --> 01:03:11.428
How many men on that crawler?

691
01:03:11.428 --> 01:03:12.549
Crew of twenty-one.

692
01:03:12.549 --> 01:03:13.949
Our ships can take six each.

693
01:03:14.088 --> 01:03:15.488
That's still three short.

694
01:03:15.888 --> 01:03:17.288
We'll find a way.

695
01:03:29.689 --> 01:03:31.848
<i>This is Duke Leto Atreides.</i>

696
01:03:31.929 --> 01:03:35.408
<i>We're coming down to extract the
crew of Delta Ajax niner.</i>

697
01:03:35.489 --> 01:03:37.409
<i>We'll set down on the west.</i>

698
01:03:47.789 --> 01:03:49.709
Shield generators weigh one hundred kilos each.

699
01:03:50.428 --> 01:03:53.148
Yes. Gurney. have our escorts throw
out the shield generators.

700
01:03:53.148 --> 01:03:54.208
Yes. sire.

701
01:03:54.208 --> 01:03:55.729
And. Paul. I want you at the back of the thopter.

702
01:03:56.508 --> 01:03:57.627
Guide them in.

703
01:03:57.627 --> 01:04:01.269
Delta Ajax niner. put seven
men each in my ships now.

704
01:04:59.988 --> 01:05:01.949
<i>Contact in two minutes.</i>

705
01:05:03.948 --> 01:05:06.668
<i>Getting close. guys. We better abandon ship now.</i>

706
01:05:08.949 --> 01:05:10.349
Where are they?

707
01:05:10.768 --> 01:05:12.729
<i>Sir. there's protocol for a reason.</i>

708
01:05:12.808 --> 01:05:15.408
<i>If we take one step out there.
we're as good as dead.</i>

709
01:05:15.489 --> 01:05:17.048
<i>Besides. we've got a full load of spice.</i>

710
01:05:17.129 --> 01:05:19.088
- <i>We can't just leave it.</i>
- Damn the spice!

711
01:05:19.169 --> 01:05:21.688
I want every man off that crawler now!

712
01:05:35.589 --> 01:05:36.709
Hey!

713
01:05:36.709 --> 01:05:37.828
Hey!

714
01:05:37.828 --> 01:05:40.269
Seven over here. seven over there.

715
01:05:42.108 --> 01:05:44.428
Go! Go! Go!

716
01:05:59.749 --> 01:06:02.588
Kwisatz Haderach.

717
01:06:15.728 --> 01:06:19.049
Kwisatz Haderach <i>awakes.</i>

718
01:06:28.129 --> 01:06:29.529
Hurry! Get on!

719
01:06:39.268 --> 01:06:40.668
It's here!

720
01:06:43.148 --> 01:06:44.548
Paul!

721
01:06:46.508 --> 01:06:47.908
Paul!

722
01:06:51.889 --> 01:06:55.168
I recognize your footsteps. old man.

723
01:06:55.808 --> 01:06:57.328
Get up!

724
01:06:57.409 --> 01:06:59.849
Let's go!

725
01:07:00.428 --> 01:07:02.948
What's the matter with you? Come on! Let's go!

726
01:07:03.028 --> 01:07:04.428
Run!

727
01:07:30.368 --> 01:07:31.768
Hey!

728
01:07:49.128 --> 01:07:51.448
Bless the Maker and His Water.

729
01:07:52.029 --> 01:07:54.148
Bless the coming and going of him.

730
01:07:54.229 --> 01:07:59.508
May His passage cleanse the world and
keep the world for His people.

731
01:08:23.508 --> 01:08:24.788
Hey!

732
01:08:24.788 --> 01:08:26.749
- You cannot take such risks.
- Yes. sir.

733
01:08:26.827 --> 01:08:28.148
You have responsibilities.

734
01:08:28.148 --> 01:08:29.308
I… I'm sorry. sir. It won't happen again.

735
01:08:29.308 --> 01:08:30.708
Go.

736
01:08:31.068 --> 01:08:32.468
Dr. Kynes.

737
01:08:34.568 --> 01:08:36.329
You saw it.

738
01:08:36.407 --> 01:08:38.327
With your own eyes. It's plain to see.

739
01:08:38.407 --> 01:08:40.568
Everything they've left us is in shambles.

740
01:08:40.648 --> 01:08:42.489
We've been set up to fail.

741
01:08:42.568 --> 01:08:45.168
That carryall was just old.

742
01:08:45.248 --> 01:08:47.208
The desert isn't kind to equipment.

743
01:08:49.508 --> 01:08:53.468
You know what will happen if I don't
get spice production back on track.

744
01:08:55.848 --> 01:08:59.529
I'm not here to take your part.

745
01:08:59.608 --> 01:09:03.487
Arrakis has seen men like you come and go.

746
01:09:06.508 --> 01:09:09.987
Take good care of your family.

747
01:09:13.189 --> 01:09:16.188
The desert's not kind to humans either.

748
01:09:32.907 --> 01:09:35.869
Spice is a psychoactive chemical.

749
01:09:36.987 --> 01:09:38.869
You seem to be sensitive.

750
01:09:43.568 --> 01:09:44.968
You'll be fine.

751
01:09:46.208 --> 01:09:48.169
Thank you. Dr. Yueh.

752
01:09:57.668 --> 01:10:00.068
That wasn't an allergic reaction.

753
01:10:01.907 --> 01:10:03.508
I had a vision.

754
01:10:05.907 --> 01:10:07.589
My eyes were wide open.

755
01:10:09.968 --> 01:10:11.368
What did you see?

756
01:10:48.888 --> 01:10:52.487
Kwisatz Haderach.

757
01:10:52.568 --> 01:10:55.489
<i>You can see.</i>

758
01:11:36.708 --> 01:11:38.308
<i>It's confusing.</i>

759
01:11:38.388 --> 01:11:42.028
<i>I thought I saw my death. only it wasn't.</i>

760
01:11:42.109 --> 01:11:45.828
<i>I know a knife is important. somehow.</i>

761
01:11:48.168 --> 01:11:54.088
<i>Someone will hand me a blade. but I
don't know who. or when. or where.</i>

762
01:11:56.588 --> 01:11:59.468
<i>Some things. though. are crystal clear.</i>

763
01:11:59.548 --> 01:12:00.947
<i>I can feel it.</i>

764
01:12:05.348 --> 01:12:06.828
<i>I know you're pregnant.</i>

765
01:12:13.168 --> 01:12:14.888
You can't know that.

766
01:12:16.368 --> 01:12:17.608
I barely know that.

767
01:12:17.608 --> 01:12:19.528
It's only been a few weeks.

768
01:13:03.859 --> 01:13:05.841
Why does the Baron need us?

769
01:13:06.190 --> 01:13:09.099
Harkonnens outnumber the Atreides.

770
01:13:10.568 --> 01:13:14.088
Atreides legions are the finest in the Imperium.

771
01:13:14.168 --> 01:13:17.317
Trained by Gurney Halleck and Duncan Idaho.

772
01:13:17.917 --> 01:13:19.677
We are the Sardaukar.

773
01:13:20.089 --> 01:13:21.489
The Emperor's blades.

774
01:13:22.056 --> 01:13:24.261
Those who stand against us fall.

775
01:13:25.368 --> 01:13:26.768
Just so.

776
01:13:27.608 --> 01:13:29.208
Three battalions.

777
01:13:29.288 --> 01:13:30.688
As agreed.

778
01:13:36.153 --> 01:13:38.915
The Emperor commands it. It is done.

779
01:14:11.288 --> 01:14:13.448
There is something you need to know about Paul.

780
01:14:13.528 --> 01:14:15.368
No.

781
01:14:15.448 --> 01:14:17.768
Don't think I want to know.

782
01:14:17.848 --> 01:14:19.768
Ever since you brought him before
your Reverend Mother.

783
01:14:19.848 --> 01:14:21.608
he hasn't been the same.

784
01:14:23.208 --> 01:14:24.607
He's distracted.

785
01:14:26.288 --> 01:14:33.068
Jessica. you gave me a son. and from the moment
he was born. I never questioned you.

786
01:14:33.148 --> 01:14:35.508
I trusted you completely.

787
01:14:35.588 --> 01:14:37.667
Even when you walked in shadows.

788
01:14:38.788 --> 01:14:40.668
Now. I'm asking you this one thing.

789
01:14:43.688 --> 01:14:48.206
If anything happens…
will you protect our son?

790
01:14:50.308 --> 01:14:51.748
With my life.

791
01:14:51.828 --> 01:14:54.148
I'm not asking his mother.
I'm asking the Bene Gesserit.

792
01:14:58.188 --> 01:15:00.148
Will you protect Paul?

793
01:15:06.008 --> 01:15:07.928
Why are you having these thoughts?

794
01:15:14.128 --> 01:15:16.568
Leto. this is not you.

795
01:15:22.428 --> 01:15:24.748
I thought we'd have more time.

796
01:15:43.908 --> 01:15:46.428
Have a good night. Master Paul.

797
01:15:46.508 --> 01:15:48.348
Good night. Dr. Yueh.

798
01:15:57.768 --> 01:15:59.168
<i>You need to sleep.</i>

799
01:16:00.888 --> 01:16:02.288
No.

800
01:16:02.288 --> 01:16:03.687
Not like that.

801
01:16:19.168 --> 01:16:21.327
I should have married you.

802
01:17:39.868 --> 01:17:41.548
Hawat. Security.

803
01:17:43.788 --> 01:17:45.187
Security.

804
01:18:48.468 --> 01:18:50.067
Sir. Sir.

805
01:18:50.908 --> 01:18:52.628
The shield's come down.

806
01:19:01.647 --> 01:19:03.528
God in heaven.

807
01:19:03.608 --> 01:19:06.447
Get everything with guns off the ground! Go!

808
01:19:50.648 --> 01:19:52.367
Go! Go! Go!

809
01:20:54.527 --> 01:20:56.447
With me! With me!

810
01:21:25.248 --> 01:21:26.367
Atreides!

811
01:21:26.367 --> 01:21:27.767
Atreides!

812
01:21:56.867 --> 01:21:59.148
- Sardaukar!
- Sardaukar!

813
01:22:21.668 --> 01:22:23.267
I'm sorry. my lord.

814
01:22:26.287 --> 01:22:29.127
but I've made a bargain with the Baron.

815
01:22:32.068 --> 01:22:33.468
Why?

816
01:22:33.868 --> 01:22:35.827
I had no choice.

817
01:22:35.908 --> 01:22:39.588
The Harkonnens have my wife. Wanna.

818
01:22:40.167 --> 01:22:42.607
They take her apart like a doll.

819
01:22:43.567 --> 01:22:47.208
I will buy her freedom. and you are the price.

820
01:22:50.408 --> 01:22:53.327
For Paul. I will do what I can.

821
01:22:54.007 --> 01:22:57.528
and you will kill a man for me.

822
01:23:02.727 --> 01:23:06.127
I'm going to replace your peg tooth.

823
01:23:06.208 --> 01:23:10.927
If you bite down hard. this tooth will crush.

824
01:23:11.008 --> 01:23:15.088
Breathe out. and you will
fill the air with poison.

825
01:23:15.167 --> 01:23:24.027
It will be your last breath. but if you choose
your moment well. it will also be the Baron's.

826
01:24:57.907 --> 01:24:59.307
Paul.

827
01:25:12.992 --> 01:25:14.996
We'll drop them in the desert.

828
01:25:16.088 --> 01:25:18.853
Let the worms have them.

829
01:25:20.445 --> 01:25:22.593
Why don't we just cut their throats?

830
01:25:23.740 --> 01:25:26.985
We could face a Truthsayer.

831
01:25:28.118 --> 01:25:30.673
We can say we didn't kill them.

832
01:25:37.907 --> 01:25:40.509
The scarred one is deaf.

833
01:26:21.887 --> 01:26:23.567
To hell. dogs!

834
01:27:59.247 --> 01:28:01.927
I've never had a highborn.

835
01:28:04.207 --> 01:28:05.567
You?

836
01:28:05.567 --> 01:28:07.567
Bene Gesserit ain't all highborn.

837
01:28:07.647 --> 01:28:11.288
She's highborn enough for me.

838
01:28:11.367 --> 01:28:15.527
Let's feed the kid to the worms.
and give her a long goodbye.

839
01:28:15.600 --> 01:28:19.000
Don't you dare touch my mother.

840
01:28:19.727 --> 01:28:21.126
Don't talk.

841
01:28:26.606 --> 01:28:28.935
Don't! You are not ready.

842
01:28:31.607 --> 01:28:33.047
Remove her gag.

843
01:28:42.767 --> 01:28:44.487
Shut up.

844
01:28:45.173 --> 01:28:47.240
Find the right pitch.

845
01:28:54.332 --> 01:28:55.761
We're far enough.

846
01:28:56.192 --> 01:28:58.168
Let's throw the boy out.

847
01:29:13.247 --> 01:29:14.647
Remove her gag.

848
01:29:20.787 --> 01:29:22.187
Kill him.

849
01:29:30.547 --> 01:29:31.947
Set us free.

850
01:29:45.587 --> 01:29:46.947
Stop!

851
01:29:46.947 --> 01:29:48.427
Cut the rope.

852
01:29:51.027 --> 01:29:52.427
Give me the knife.

853
01:30:00.787 --> 01:30:03.747
Your pitch was too forced.

854
01:30:12.307 --> 01:30:13.827
It's a fremkit.

855
01:30:26.767 --> 01:30:28.166
They've crippled the ship.

856
01:31:40.967 --> 01:31:42.367
Mmm.

857
01:32:00.147 --> 01:32:01.547
Ah.

858
01:32:02.907 --> 01:32:05.867
You have a wonderful kitchen. cousin.

859
01:32:24.307 --> 01:32:27.027
This is Dr. Yueh's handwriting.

860
01:32:27.107 --> 01:32:31.707
“If anyone makes it out of Arrakeen alive. there's
an Atreides beacon in the fremkit.”

861
01:32:31.787 --> 01:32:34.426
“God willing. they'll
be able to find you.”

862
01:32:42.467 --> 01:32:43.867
My lord Baron.

863
01:32:44.827 --> 01:32:46.027
Dr. Yueh.

864
01:32:46.027 --> 01:32:47.626
The traitor.

865
01:32:48.787 --> 01:32:50.187
What do you want?

866
01:32:50.987 --> 01:32:55.147
I jammed their comms and lowered their shields.

867
01:32:55.227 --> 01:32:56.626
Hmm.

868
01:32:56.706 --> 01:32:58.867
I delivered the Duke and his family.

869
01:32:58.946 --> 01:33:04.127
The bargain to the letter. and
what was I to do for you?

870
01:33:04.707 --> 01:33:06.787
Deliver my wife from her agony.

871
01:33:08.627 --> 01:33:10.027
Yes.

872
01:33:43.247 --> 01:33:45.767
I said I'd set her free.

873
01:33:45.847 --> 01:33:47.606
That you could join her.

874
01:33:51.566 --> 01:33:53.407
So. join her.

875
01:34:02.927 --> 01:34:05.087
What do you think is next?

876
01:34:08.607 --> 01:34:10.806
It's a thumper.

877
01:34:10.887 --> 01:34:12.407
No stillsuits.

878
01:34:12.487 --> 01:34:14.327
The one thing we actually need.

879
01:34:19.707 --> 01:34:25.907
For hundreds of years. we've traded
blood for blood. but no more.

880
01:34:27.307 --> 01:34:31.387
Your son is dead. Your concubine is dead.

881
01:34:31.466 --> 01:34:39.867
Tonight the house of Atreides falls.
and your bloodline ends forever.

882
01:34:53.507 --> 01:34:54.907
What did you say?

883
01:35:04.146 --> 01:35:05.546
Here I am…

884
01:35:06.787 --> 01:35:08.507
<i>here I remain.</i>

885
01:36:53.007 --> 01:36:54.407
Kynes!

886
01:36:55.367 --> 01:36:57.087
It's not safe for you here.

887
01:36:57.166 --> 01:36:59.847
Will you tell the Great Houses of the
Landsraad how we were betrayed?

888
01:36:59.926 --> 01:37:02.406
How the best of them were murdered?

889
01:37:02.487 --> 01:37:05.047
I am commanded to say nothing.

890
01:37:05.966 --> 01:37:07.606
To see nothing.

891
01:37:09.867 --> 01:37:12.147
The Emperor sent us here to die.

892
01:38:00.887 --> 01:38:03.166
There's spice in the tent.

893
01:39:28.786 --> 01:39:31.627
That's the future. It's coming.

894
01:39:46.087 --> 01:39:49.687
Holy war spreading across the universe
like unquenchable fire.

895
01:40:02.426 --> 01:40:05.227
Paul. you're scared. I can see it.

896
01:40:05.306 --> 01:40:08.267
Tell me. please. what do you fear?

897
01:40:17.366 --> 01:40:19.767
Somebody help me. please.

898
01:40:20.947 --> 01:40:22.347
Paul.

899
01:40:24.266 --> 01:40:25.906
It's coming.

900
01:40:25.987 --> 01:40:29.267
<i>I see a holy war spreading across the
universe like unquenchable fire.</i>

901
01:40:29.346 --> 01:40:34.006
A warrior religion that waves the Atreides
banner in my father's name.

902
01:40:34.006 --> 01:40:34.966
Paul.

903
01:40:34.966 --> 01:40:36.566
Fanatical legions worshipping

904
01:40:36.647 --> 01:40:38.727
<i>at the shrine of my father's skull.</i>

905
01:40:39.527 --> 01:40:41.887
<i>A war in my name!</i>

906
01:40:41.966 --> 01:40:43.726
Everyone's shouting my name!

907
01:40:44.307 --> 01:40:45.706
Paul.

908
01:40:48.787 --> 01:40:50.786
Paul Atreides.

909
01:40:50.867 --> 01:40:53.706
You are your father's son. You are my son.

910
01:40:53.786 --> 01:40:57.147
You are the Duke Paul Atreides.

911
01:40:57.726 --> 01:41:00.407
You know who you are. You know who you are.

912
01:41:00.486 --> 01:41:01.885
Get off me!

913
01:41:03.447 --> 01:41:05.046
You did this to me!

914
01:41:05.126 --> 01:41:07.726
You Bene Gesserit made me a freak!

915
01:41:32.807 --> 01:41:35.007
My father is dead.

916
01:42:12.007 --> 01:42:13.446
Someone's near.

917
01:42:14.327 --> 01:42:15.766
You need to drink.

918
01:42:17.286 --> 01:42:19.486
It's recycled water from the tent.

919
01:42:27.466 --> 01:42:29.186
Sweat and tears.

920
01:42:33.206 --> 01:42:34.846
All right. let's get out of here.

921
01:43:48.086 --> 01:43:49.766
That's Duncan.

922
01:43:57.066 --> 01:43:58.465
Duncan.

923
01:43:59.826 --> 01:44:01.066
My lady.

924
01:44:01.066 --> 01:44:02.465
Paul.

925
01:44:02.507 --> 01:44:04.786
I'm so sorry. Your father—

926
01:44:04.866 --> 01:44:06.266
We know.

927
01:44:07.867 --> 01:44:09.267
My lord Duke.

928
01:44:23.346 --> 01:44:24.746
Here.

929
01:44:26.306 --> 01:44:27.746
Drink this.

930
01:44:34.706 --> 01:44:38.766
Harkonnens hit every population
center on the planet at once.

931
01:44:38.846 --> 01:44:40.886
There must have been ten legions.
hundreds of ships.

932
01:44:40.966 --> 01:44:42.926
There were Sardaukar with them.

933
01:44:43.206 --> 01:44:45.646
- At least two battalions.
- What? Are you sure?

934
01:44:45.726 --> 01:44:49.766
You cross swords with a Sardaukar. you know it.

935
01:44:50.766 --> 01:44:55.326
So. the Emperor's taken a side.

936
01:44:55.406 --> 01:44:58.406
What says the Judge of the Change?

937
01:44:58.486 --> 01:45:00.446
The Emperor forbids me from
saying anything at all.

938
01:45:00.526 --> 01:45:02.406
And yet you risk your life to help us.

939
01:45:23.046 --> 01:45:24.686
Storm's coming.

940
01:45:38.506 --> 01:45:40.666
The storm will be here in a few hours.

941
01:45:40.746 --> 01:45:42.146
We'll be safe here.

942
01:45:43.306 --> 01:45:45.466
Do you know what this place is?

943
01:45:45.546 --> 01:45:47.867
It's an old ecological testing station.

944
01:45:51.606 --> 01:45:53.366
They were meant to tame the planet.

945
01:45:53.447 --> 01:45:55.766
Free the water locked beneath the sands.

946
01:45:58.646 --> 01:46:01.166
Arrakis could have been a paradise.

947
01:46:01.246 --> 01:46:04.007
The work had begun. but then
the spice was discovered.

948
01:46:04.086 --> 01:46:06.966
and suddenly no one wanted the desert to go away.

949
01:46:07.046 --> 01:46:10.306
Tanat. will you find stillsuits
to fit our visitors?

950
01:46:10.386 --> 01:46:11.666
Yes. Liet.

951
01:46:11.666 --> 01:46:13.066
Shamir. a coffee service. please.

952
01:46:13.106 --> 01:46:14.506
Of course. Liet.

953
01:46:16.746 --> 01:46:18.586
Who are you to the Fremen?

954
01:47:09.046 --> 01:47:12.326
You know what the Great Houses
fear most. Dr. Kynes?

955
01:47:13.526 --> 01:47:15.686
Exactly what has happened to us here.

956
01:47:16.646 --> 01:47:19.486
The Sardaukar coming and picking
them off one by one.

957
01:47:22.826 --> 01:47:25.906
Only together can they stand a
chance against the Imperium.

958
01:47:27.866 --> 01:47:29.946
Would you bear witness?

959
01:47:30.026 --> 01:47:33.026
Testify that the Emperor has
moved against us here?

960
01:47:33.106 --> 01:47:40.826
If they believe me. there would be General warfare
between the Great Houses and the Emperor.

961
01:47:40.906 --> 01:47:43.906
Chaos. across the Imperium.

962
01:47:43.986 --> 01:47:47.786
Suppose I presented the Emperor
with an alternative to chaos.

963
01:47:47.866 --> 01:47:51.706
The Emperor has no sons. and his
daughters have yet to marry.

964
01:47:51.786 --> 01:47:54.466
You'd make a play for the throne?

965
01:47:54.546 --> 01:47:56.226
The Emperor feared the Atreides.

966
01:47:56.806 --> 01:47:58.406
He brought you here to kill you.

967
01:47:58.486 --> 01:48:00.886
What don't you understand?

968
01:48:00.966 --> 01:48:04.006
You're a lost boy hiding in a hole in the ground.

969
01:48:08.546 --> 01:48:11.186
The Fremen speak of the <i>Lisan al-Gaib.</i>

970
01:48:12.146 --> 01:48:13.906
Careful.

971
01:48:13.986 --> 01:48:17.266
The Voice from the outer world who
will lead them to paradise.

972
01:48:18.546 --> 01:48:19.946
Superstition.

973
01:48:24.806 --> 01:48:27.965
I know you loved a Fremen warrior
and lost him in battle.

974
01:48:30.886 --> 01:48:34.446
I know you walk in two worlds
and are known by many names.

975
01:48:39.986 --> 01:48:41.786
I've seen your dream.

976
01:48:46.246 --> 01:48:50.886
As emperor. Dr. Kynes. I could make a paradise
of Arrakis with a wave of my hand.

977
01:48:53.486 --> 01:48:56.228
Do you really think he is the Mahdi?

978
01:48:57.236 --> 01:48:59.028
He looks young to me.

979
01:50:46.926 --> 01:50:48.326
Sardaukar!

980
01:50:50.926 --> 01:50:52.166
No! Duncan!

981
01:50:52.166 --> 01:50:53.566
Paul. no!

982
01:50:53.946 --> 01:50:55.346
- Duncan. no!
- No!

983
01:50:56.306 --> 01:50:57.706
- No!
- Paul. no!

984
01:50:58.706 --> 01:51:00.026
Duncan. no!

985
01:51:00.026 --> 01:51:02.386
- He's locked the door.
- Duncan! No!

986
01:51:51.746 --> 01:51:53.266
He's gone.

987
01:51:53.346 --> 01:51:54.466
Duncan!

988
01:51:54.466 --> 01:51:55.986
We have to go. We have no choice.

989
01:52:03.266 --> 01:52:05.586
Paul. go! Paul!

990
01:52:25.206 --> 01:52:26.806
Come on. Come on. come on!

991
01:52:58.886 --> 01:53:02.686
Follow the light. You'll find
a thopter ready to fly.

992
01:53:02.765 --> 01:53:04.566
That storm out there is your best shot.

993
01:53:04.646 --> 01:53:07.126
Above five thousand meters. it's mostly dust.

994
01:53:07.206 --> 01:53:11.166
Climb into it. Stay on top. Head
south. Find the Fremen.

995
01:53:11.245 --> 01:53:12.526
Are you not coming with us?

996
01:53:12.526 --> 01:53:13.766
It only seats two.

997
01:53:13.766 --> 01:53:17.126
I'll go to the next station and report
this attack to the Landsraad.

998
01:53:17.206 --> 01:53:18.606
How?

999
01:53:19.666 --> 01:53:21.505
I'm Fremen.

1000
01:53:21.586 --> 01:53:23.705
The desert's my home.

1001
01:53:23.786 --> 01:53:26.306
- Good luck.
- Good luck.

1002
01:56:03.997 --> 01:56:06.779
Kynes. You have betrayed the Emperor.

1003
01:56:06.846 --> 01:56:09.166
I serve only one master.

1004
01:56:09.245 --> 01:56:12.446
His name is <i>Shai-Hulud.</i>

1005
01:56:58.346 --> 01:56:59.866
There are jet flares behind us.

1006
01:57:33.805 --> 01:57:35.646
Paul. We're not high enough!

1007
01:58:08.246 --> 01:58:09.606
I must not fear.

1008
01:58:09.606 --> 01:58:11.205
Fear is the mind-killer.

1009
01:58:11.286 --> 01:58:14.885
Fear is the little death that brings obliteration.

1010
01:58:20.245 --> 01:58:23.086
<i>See the friend.</i>

1011
01:58:26.724 --> 01:58:29.485
<i>See the friend.</i>

1012
01:58:32.885 --> 01:58:35.565
<i>The mystery of life isn't a problem to solve…</i>

1013
01:58:38.645 --> 01:58:40.925
<i>but a reality to experience.</i>

1014
01:58:44.085 --> 01:58:48.485
A process that cannot be understood
by stopping it.

1015
01:58:49.066 --> 01:58:51.386
We must move with the flow of the process.

1016
01:58:52.305 --> 01:58:54.706
<i>We must join it.</i>

1017
01:58:54.785 --> 01:58:56.505
<i>We must flow with it.</i>

1018
01:58:56.586 --> 01:58:58.145
<i>Let go.</i>

1019
01:58:58.226 --> 01:59:00.146
<i>Let go.</i>

1020
01:59:34.436 --> 01:59:36.879
His healing isn't complete.

1021
01:59:47.865 --> 01:59:51.825
We chased them into a Coriolis storm.

1022
01:59:53.265 --> 01:59:55.745
Winds at eight hundred kilometers an hour.

1023
02:00:00.225 --> 02:00:02.425
Nothing survives such a storm.

1024
02:00:02.506 --> 02:00:03.906
They're dead.

1025
02:00:05.226 --> 02:00:06.985
It's a certainty.

1026
02:00:14.405 --> 02:00:16.605
So. it's done. Finally.

1027
02:00:18.645 --> 02:00:26.505
Send word to Giedi Prime to begin selling
our spice reserves. but slowly.

1028
02:00:26.586 --> 02:00:29.145
We don't want the price to fall.

1029
02:00:29.225 --> 02:00:33.145
You have no idea how much it cost me
to bring such a force to bear here.

1030
02:00:33.225 --> 02:00:35.985
Now. I only have one requirement.

1031
02:00:36.566 --> 02:00:37.965
Income.

1032
02:00:38.445 --> 02:00:40.165
So. squeeze. Rabban.

1033
02:00:40.885 --> 02:00:42.285
Squeeze hard.

1034
02:00:42.365 --> 02:00:43.764
Yes. Uncle.

1035
02:00:45.206 --> 02:00:46.606
And the Fremen?

1036
02:00:47.365 --> 02:00:48.764
Kill them all.

1037
02:01:12.846 --> 02:01:14.725
We're above five thousand meters.

1038
02:02:52.684 --> 02:02:54.566
As soon as we land. run for the rocks.

1039
02:04:47.385 --> 02:04:49.145
And breathe through this.

1040
02:05:19.605 --> 02:05:21.805
<i>Now. we have to find the Fremen.</i>

1041
02:05:23.285 --> 02:05:24.645
<i>Are you good?</i>

1042
02:05:24.645 --> 02:05:26.045
<i>Yeah.</i>

1043
02:06:33.585 --> 02:06:35.265
<i>Paul…</i>

1044
02:06:41.245 --> 02:06:44.924
<i>don't be frightened.</i>

1045
02:06:45.005 --> 02:06:48.084
<i>Even a little desert mouse can survive.</i>

1046
02:06:49.085 --> 02:06:52.125
<i>Don't be frightened.</i>

1047
02:06:52.205 --> 02:06:53.965
<i>You'll need to face your fears.</i>

1048
02:06:54.045 --> 02:06:55.565
<i>A friend…</i>

1049
02:06:55.644 --> 02:06:58.644
<i>a friend will help you.</i>

1050
02:07:00.765 --> 02:07:02.525
<i>Follow the friend.</i>

1051
02:07:05.245 --> 02:07:06.644
<i>You have much to learn.</i>

1052
02:07:08.645 --> 02:07:11.325
and I will show you the ways of the desert.

1053
02:07:14.524 --> 02:07:16.045
Come with me.

1054
02:07:44.525 --> 02:07:50.285
<i>The</i> Sietch <i>where Duncan lived
is somewhere off that way.</i>

1055
02:07:52.365 --> 02:07:55.245
<i>I can see greenery over there.</i>

1056
02:07:55.325 --> 02:07:56.525
<i>There.</i>

1057
02:07:56.525 --> 02:07:58.445
<i>That means Fremen live there.</i>

1058
02:08:03.104 --> 02:08:05.145
<i>We'll cross after dark.</i>

1059
02:08:05.225 --> 02:08:07.145
<i>That's how the Fremen do it.</i>

1060
02:08:10.485 --> 02:08:12.885
<i>We're about to enter worm territory.</i>

1061
02:08:12.965 --> 02:08:14.724
<i>We can't walk like regular humans.</i>

1062
02:08:14.805 --> 02:08:16.205
<i>If we do. we're dead.</i>

1063
02:08:16.245 --> 02:08:18.165
<i>We'll have to walk like the Fremen do.</i>

1064
02:08:18.245 --> 02:08:19.725
<i>It's called a sandwalk.</i>

1065
02:08:19.804 --> 02:08:22.365
<i>At least according to the filmbooks back home.</i>

1066
02:08:22.445 --> 02:08:23.845
<i>Yeah. Yeah. okay.</i>

1067
02:08:23.885 --> 02:08:25.365
<i>Okay. Follow me.</i>

1068
02:08:25.445 --> 02:08:27.125
<i>Do the same moves.</i>

1069
02:08:40.765 --> 02:08:42.324
<i>I think this is the right direction.</i>

1070
02:10:05.025 --> 02:10:06.425
<i>It's close by.</i>

1071
02:10:06.905 --> 02:10:08.745
<i>Let's get out of here.</i>

1072
02:10:10.545 --> 02:10:13.305
<i>Wait.</i>

1073
02:10:13.384 --> 02:10:15.185
<i>It's drum sand.</i>

1074
02:10:19.625 --> 02:10:21.505
<i>Run.</i>

1075
02:10:27.185 --> 02:10:28.825
<i>Go! Go!</i>

1076
02:11:40.984 --> 02:11:42.384
<i>It's a thumper.</i>

1077
02:11:47.144 --> 02:11:49.064
<i>Someone set off a thumper.</i>

1078
02:12:04.025 --> 02:12:06.185
<i>Paul! Run!</i>

1079
02:12:20.264 --> 02:12:21.624
How big are they?

1080
02:12:21.624 --> 02:12:23.023
That was insane.

1081
02:12:27.805 --> 02:12:29.284
Someone called it.

1082
02:12:39.532 --> 02:12:41.702
We are not alone.

1083
02:13:01.425 --> 02:13:03.865
<i>Do not run.</i>

1084
02:13:03.944 --> 02:13:06.465
<i>You will only waste your body's water.</i>

1085
02:13:07.925 --> 02:13:09.325
<i>Hold.</i>

1086
02:13:16.285 --> 02:13:17.204
Stilgar.

1087
02:13:17.204 --> 02:13:18.724
Hey!

1088
02:13:18.805 --> 02:13:21.764
You know me. I was there when you
came to my father's council.

1089
02:13:22.344 --> 02:13:23.344
Oh.

1090
02:13:23.344 --> 02:13:25.305
This is the Duke's son.

1091
02:13:25.384 --> 02:13:26.945
Why are you waiting?

1092
02:13:27.024 --> 02:13:28.824
We need their water.

1093
02:13:28.905 --> 02:13:31.065
This is the boy I told you about.

1094
02:13:31.144 --> 02:13:32.544
We can't touch him.

1095
02:13:33.880 --> 02:13:35.760
How can he be the Lisan al-Gaib?

1096
02:13:36.006 --> 02:13:38.364
- He hasn't proven himself.
- They are weaklings.

1097
02:13:38.445 --> 02:13:40.124
Jamis.

1098
02:13:40.205 --> 02:13:44.844
That was a brave crossing they made in the path of <i>Shai-Hulud.</i>

1099
02:13:45.424 --> 02:13:48.425
He does not speak or act like a weakling.

1100
02:13:49.424 --> 02:13:51.064
Nor did his father.

1101
02:13:51.145 --> 02:13:53.664
My thumper saved his life.

1102
02:13:53.745 --> 02:13:56.105
Go back to reason. Stilgar.

1103
02:13:56.184 --> 02:13:57.824
He's not the one.

1104
02:14:00.965 --> 02:14:02.564
We have powerful friends.

1105
02:14:02.645 --> 02:14:07.544
You help us off-world. to Caladan. you will be well rewarded.

1106
02:14:07.544 --> 02:14:11.785
What wealth can you offer beyond
the water in your flesh?

1107
02:14:14.464 --> 02:14:18.065
Hmm… the boy is young.

1108
02:14:18.144 --> 02:14:20.265
He can learn our ways.

1109
02:14:20.344 --> 02:14:29.685
He may have sanctuary. but the woman is
untrained… and too old to learn.

1110
02:15:02.764 --> 02:15:04.804
Back. you dogs.

1111
02:15:04.864 --> 02:15:06.985
She'll cut my throat.

1112
02:15:12.244 --> 02:15:14.644
Why didn't you say you were a weirding woman?

1113
02:15:14.725 --> 02:15:16.324
And a fighter?

1114
02:15:16.405 --> 02:15:18.484
Conversation ran short.

1115
02:15:18.565 --> 02:15:20.684
Peace. woman.

1116
02:15:20.765 --> 02:15:22.165
Peace.

1117
02:15:22.804 --> 02:15:24.284
I judged too hastily.

1118
02:15:33.718 --> 02:15:35.372
The sun is rising.

1119
02:15:36.285 --> 02:15:38.146
We must reach Sietch Tabr.

1120
02:15:39.986 --> 02:15:42.124
The fates of these strangers
will be decided there.

1121
02:15:47.741 --> 02:15:49.341
Until then…

1122
02:15:49.866 --> 02:15:51.977
they have my countenance.

1123
02:15:53.989 --> 02:15:55.834
My word is on them.

1124
02:16:04.384 --> 02:16:06.704
<i>I would not have let you hurt my friends.</i>

1125
02:16:31.944 --> 02:16:36.265
They say you're the <i>Mahdi.</i>
but you look like a little boy.

1126
02:16:37.704 --> 02:16:39.104
You chose the hardest way up.

1127
02:16:39.185 --> 02:16:40.585
Follow me.

1128
02:16:43.936 --> 02:16:45.532
We must go!

1129
02:16:47.624 --> 02:16:49.144
Give it to me.

1130
02:16:56.784 --> 02:17:00.345
You will have your own maula pistol
when you've earned it.

1131
02:17:00.423 --> 02:17:01.824
Give it to me.

1132
02:17:06.944 --> 02:17:08.985
Chani. take charge of the newcomers.

1133
02:17:09.064 --> 02:17:11.585
See that they are safe on the journey. Let's go.

1134
02:17:11.664 --> 02:17:13.064
I will not have them.

1135
02:17:20.165 --> 02:17:21.565
Jamis.

1136
02:17:21.604 --> 02:17:23.844
I have spoken. Be still.

1137
02:17:23.923 --> 02:17:28.204
You talk like a leader. but the strongest leads.

1138
02:17:29.444 --> 02:17:31.164
She bested you.

1139
02:17:33.525 --> 02:17:35.724
I invoke the amtal.

1140
02:17:35.804 --> 02:17:38.124
You may not challenge a <i>Sayyadina.</i>

1141
02:17:38.204 --> 02:17:39.644
Then who will fight in her name?

1142
02:17:39.724 --> 02:17:42.364
Jamis. don't do this.

1143
02:17:42.444 --> 02:17:44.444
Don't. The night is fading.

1144
02:17:44.524 --> 02:17:47.324
Then the sun will witness this death.

1145
02:17:47.404 --> 02:17:49.364
Where is her champion?

1146
02:18:00.764 --> 02:18:02.684
I accept her champion.

1147
02:18:34.524 --> 02:18:44.485
<i>Paul Atreides must die… for k</i>wisatz
haderach to<i> rise.</i>

1148
02:18:48.044 --> 02:18:51.604
<i>Don't be frightened.</i>

1149
02:18:51.684 --> 02:18:53.204
<i>Don't resist.</i>

1150
02:18:59.503 --> 02:19:04.304
<i>When you take a life. you take your own.</i>

1151
02:19:36.284 --> 02:19:42.043
I don't believe you're the <i>Lisan al-Gaib.</i> but I want you to die with honor.

1152
02:19:53.044 --> 02:19:55.764
This crysknife was given to me by my great aunt.

1153
02:19:59.383 --> 02:20:01.663
It's made from a tooth of <i>Shai-Hulud.</i>

1154
02:20:01.743 --> 02:20:03.383
The great sandworm.

1155
02:20:04.945 --> 02:20:07.624
This will be a great honor.
for you to die holding it.

1156
02:20:12.743 --> 02:20:15.024
Where is the Outworlder?

1157
02:20:19.184 --> 02:20:21.025
Jamis is a good fighter.

1158
02:20:21.944 --> 02:20:23.543
He won't let you suffer.

1159
02:20:24.944 --> 02:20:26.505
Chani…

1160
02:20:29.503 --> 02:20:30.903
um…

1161
02:20:38.723 --> 02:20:40.124
never mind.

1162
02:21:35.964 --> 02:21:38.043
May thy knife chip and shatter.

1163
02:21:45.524 --> 02:21:47.403
You should welcome my blade.

1164
02:21:51.264 --> 02:21:52.944
This world will kill you.

1165
02:21:56.184 --> 02:21:57.663
Quicker this way.

1166
02:22:37.663 --> 02:22:39.224
Do you yield?

1167
02:22:41.384 --> 02:22:43.184
The boy doesn't know our rule.

1168
02:22:44.044 --> 02:22:45.563
There's no yielding under the amtal rule.

1169
02:22:46.143 --> 02:22:48.243
Only death is the test of it.

1170
02:22:55.823 --> 02:22:57.663
- Is he toying with him?
- No.

1171
02:22:59.944 --> 02:23:01.544
Paul has never killed a man.

1172
02:23:11.864 --> 02:23:16.104
Kwisatz Haderach.

1173
02:23:19.524 --> 02:23:22.444
Kwisatz Haderach.

1174
02:23:22.524 --> 02:23:26.243
<i>Climb up. Rise.</i>

1175
02:25:19.044 --> 02:25:20.884
You're one of us now.

1176
02:25:20.964 --> 02:25:22.724
A life for a life.

1177
02:25:22.804 --> 02:25:24.764
Come with us to <i>Sietch</i> Tabr.

1178
02:25:24.844 --> 02:25:25.922
No.

1179
02:25:25.922 --> 02:25:27.403
Paul needs to get off-world.

1180
02:25:27.483 --> 02:25:30.844
You must have ways. You have
smugglers. you have ships.

1181
02:25:30.844 --> 02:25:32.884
- No.
- You have—

1182
02:25:32.964 --> 02:25:34.964
The Emperor sent us to this place.

1183
02:25:36.823 --> 02:25:38.502
and my father came.

1184
02:25:39.384 --> 02:25:41.583
not for spice.

1185
02:25:41.662 --> 02:25:43.864
not for the riches.

1186
02:25:43.944 --> 02:25:45.983
but for the strength of your people.

1187
02:25:49.364 --> 02:25:51.364
My road leads into the desert.

1188
02:25:53.923 --> 02:25:55.323
I can see it.

1189
02:25:57.643 --> 02:26:01.604
If you'll have us. we will come.

1190
02:26:50.743 --> 02:26:52.184
Desert power.

1191
02:26:53.423 --> 02:26:55.063
This is only the beginning.

1192
